Bon Ami works great, available at any discount store or market. Make a
paste, use old diapers and polish till your hearts content. Most chrome
polishes are just another form of Bon Ami in a high priced paste form. Been
around since before me (and thats a long time), it also works great on
headlight rings, tail light bezels, and anything else chrome. Old school hot
rodders would polish their primer with it then put on a coat of kerosene to
get it to sheen.

ronnie  been there done that

